        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks GdeS for his "Études sur la végétation" [<hi rend="italic">Ann. Sci. Nat. (Bot.)</hi> 5th ser. 15 (1872): 277–315]. "Nothing can be more important … than your evidence of the extremely slow and gradual manner in which specific forms change."</p>  
<p>Hopes GdeS will shed light on whether polymorphic forms like <hi rend="italic">Rubus</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Hieracium</hi> are generating new species at present; CD doubts this.</p> 
        </abstract>
